author: Shelley Ng
title: 2 dead in Gage County, Neb., small plane crash; FAA and NTSB called to investigate - @Channel8ABC
text:
2 dead in small plane crash in Gage County 2 dead in small plane crash in Gage County Posted: 
Posted By: KLKN Newsroom 
8@klkntv.com 
Two people are dead after a plane crash in Gage County. Gage County Deputies say it happened near southwest 29th and West Ash Rd. just before 9 Saturday morning. 
Deputies say two people were inside the small 2–man airplane when it crashed in a field near Cortland. They say both died at the scene. 
Only one person has been identified at this time, that information hasn't been released yet. 
The FAA and National Transportation Safety Board were called in to investigate. According to the FAA the plane was a RV-4 aircraft and it burned on impact. 
The NSTB will start their investigation tomorrow. No word yet on what caused the crash.
